LIOTTA was bumped at the start then stumbled awkwardly and nearly unseated the rider, was taken up some while the rider regained centering in the saddle, spotted the front a few lengths, was urged early then settled off the pace, dropped back four wide around the turn and had nothing left. EXCALIBRATE leaned out at the start, disputed the pace on the inside of two foes, dropped back early on the turn and stopped.
